In this case, both Chef and Waiter classes have more than one responsibility. Specifically, they are responsible for serving food, cleaning tables, managing inventory, cooking meals, preparing desserts, and preparing drinks. This is a violation of the SRP because each class has more than one reason to change (i.e., it has more than one job).

To refactor this code to comply with the Single Responsibility Principle, we could split these responsibilities into separate classes:

