    public void pause() { Console.WriteLine("CD is paused."); }
    public void stop() { Console.WriteLine("CD stopped."); }
    public void skipTrack() { Console.WriteLine("Skipping to next CD track."); }
}

public class VinylPlayer : IMusicPlayer 
{
    public void play() { Console.WriteLine("Vinyl record is playing."); }
    public void pause() { Console.WriteLine("Vinyl playback paused (lift the needle)."); }
    public void stop() { Console.WriteLine("Vinyl playback stopped."); }
}
```
In this refactored code, we have created two separate interfaces IMusicPlayer and ISkipTrack which are smaller and more specialized. CDPlayer implements both of these interfaces while VinylPlayer only implements the first one. This way, each class has a single responsibility and clients can use them without being forced to depend on methods they don't need.

